      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey i'm struggling with a shopify theme. on mobile the product image is totally overlapping the title and description, it looks like a mess. i checked the css but cant see why it's happening on small screens. \n\nhere is the snippet i'm working with:\n\n.product-single__media {\n  float: left;\n  width: 50%;\n}\n\n.product-single__info {\n  float: right;\n  width: 50%;\n}\n\nany idea why this is breaking on mobile?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Ah, the classic issue with floating elements and mobile responsiveness. It sounds like your product images and info are getting too close to each other on smaller screens, causing an overlap. I suggest you try using media queries to adjust the widths and positions for mobile devices. Something like this should help:\n\n```css\n@media only screen and (max-width: 600px) {\n  .product-single__media,\n  .product-single__info {\n    float: none;\n    width: 100%;\n  }\n}\n```\n\nThis should give you a better layout on mobile. Remember, sometimes you have to play with the CSS a bit to get it just right. Good luck!",
