      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks that worked for the overlap, but now the spacing feels weird. like the image is too close to the text once they stack on top of each other. it looks cramped. how can i add some breathing room between the image and the title on mobile specifically?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Ah, I see what you mean. Adding some space between the image and the text can definitely help with the cramped feeling. You can use margin or padding to create some breathing room. Here's an example of how you might adjust the CSS:\n\n```css\n@media only screen and (max-width: 600px) {\n  .product-single__media,\n  .product-single__info {\n    float: none;\n    width: 100%;\n  }\n\n  .product-single__media {\n    margin-bottom: 20px; /* Adjust this value as needed */\n  }\n}\n```\n\nThis will add a bottom margin to your product image, creating some space between it and the product info. Adjust the value to get the spacing just right for your design. Remember, the key is to experiment and find the perfect balance for your theme. Good luck!",
      "source": "target",
